Results._refObjectName: As a user, I can modify the displayed text for a product attribute and the customization is saved on my report. QC ID=109,110
Results.Description:
There has to be some sort of way to indicate that the user has modified the data with some audit trail because it is VERY concerning.

Assumption: the "override" values are not stored in the system for re-running the report in the future. A report re-run will not apply previously overridden values.

Web: When the user makes a change, that logged in user's name is the source of the value.
If there was an original source, it is wiped out.
Marking is changed to Proprietary by default. "Source designation"
Results.Name: As a user, I can modify the displayed text for a product attribute and the customization is saved on my report. QC ID=109,110
